snippet.title: The Next Generation of Heroes? 😂 | Superpower Tryouts at Zoom Academy! #movie #shorts #edit
snippet.description: Step into one of the most hilarious and heartwarming scenes from Zoom: Academy for Superheroes, where kids from across the country show up to audition for the ultimate honor—becoming the next generation of superheroes! 💥From invisibility mishaps to super strength that’s just a bit too strong, this tryout session is anything but ordinary. Led by the reluctant hero Captain Zoom, the team searches for young recruits who might save the world—or at least survive training camp! 😄Watch as each kid reveals their quirky and sometimes unpredictable powers. Some impress, some cause a few laughs (and minor explosions), but all of them have something special. It's a chaotic mix of chaos, comedy, and surprising moments of heart. ❤️Whether you're here for the action, the laughs, or the nostalgia of early 2000s superhero films, this scene is a must-watch. snippet.title: Politicians in parliament involved in crime syndicate: Nhlanhla Mkhwanazi
snippet.description:
KwaZulu-Natal Provincial Police Commissioner, Lieutenant General Nhlanhla Mkhwanazi, has implicated some senior SAPS officials of involvement in corruption. 
He briefed the media on operational matters in the province today.
He has accused Police Minister Senzo Mchunu of being in constant communication with people involved in criminal activities. Mkhwanazi also says police have been in possession of firearms linked to the killing of high-profile South Africans, including artists in Gauteng, but no action has been taken.


For more news, visit sabcnews.com and #SABCNews on all Social Media platforms.
